<br>
The continient is divided into 3 sections, the East, the West and the North by a large forest.<br>
<br>
The Republic's capitol is in the West.  It has three large circular cities with high population densities with the slums on the outskirts to the richer center of the city 'disk' reaching a massive spire that is the main commerical center that reminds everyone who's incharge.  All three cities are designed like this.<br>
<br>
The Republic is ruled by a Senate, represents the people; Emperor, elected by the senate; and Military, who represents the needs of the military/police to enforce the regulations and defend the borders.<br>
<br>
Also in the West is the Hiro-Energy Corporation(H-Corp) which is a massive energy monopoly, it markets Hydrogen, the comodity that all modern life is dependant on, and most vehicles.  H-Corp uses massive tidal generators and seperators off shore to produce the Hydrogen.  They also hold a near monopoly on air transport, they have a massive air fleet to move the Hydrogen around from Wast to East.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The East is basically a large plain/deciduous forest containing the independent city states which trade amongst themselves.  Rein City, a mining town; Kytan, the largest commercial trading city; Joru, the second largest city, it handles the main land trade; Stove Pipe, the industrial village; and Port Fredrick; another large port city.<br>
<br>
It exists in relative harmony.  Each town is governed independantly.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Then the North.  The North is a barren stretch of desert in a massive depression that spans the length of half the continent.  It is desolate and a place where the Republic uses to exile people to.  In the North there exists a strict tribal system.  Each side is usually warring with one another.<br>
<br>
Their government is dependent from tribe to tribe.  The North is relatively chaotic, civil wars, slavers, bandits, mercs.... etc<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The BG Story:<br>
<br>
The H-Corporation, seeking to expand and secure the market in the East from gangsters, enlists the reluctant Republic to enforce their requests.  After flying over several thousand troops along with the famous General Titus Leone over to the small frontier outpost of 'Gibralter'.  They decide to begin with the large port city of Kytan, the most resistant to H-Corp's requests to enforce illegal Hydrogen Traficcing.<br>
<br>
The Republic forces occupy Kytan to the protests of just about everyone, a curfew is enacted and the Republic goes around, arresting trafficcers.  The people in the East thinks this is actually the prerequisite to invasion, something that the Republic doesn't want to do, and begin to mobilize.  This act also begins to collapse the fragile economy of the East.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the residents of Kytan defy the curfew and protest infront of the Governer's Mansion, the occupation HQ.  The military breaks it up fairly quickly without lethal force and arrest several prominent civilians.  Later that week, another protest, this time much bigger, just aobut everyone in the city ours into the streets and overwhelms the military on the street(only a few thousand troops actually occupy the city, the rest are in reserve) and march to the Governer's Mansion.  This time it is broken up with lethal force, about one hundred people die.<br>
<br>
This is known as the Kytan Massacre.  The man implicated, General Titus Leone, circumstancial evidence links him to an order to fire on the civilians.  Convinient for the Senate who views him as a threat to power, he has a great support base.  He is slated to be executed but hsi loyal troops smuggle him into the north where he has not been heard from since.<br>
<br>
Protests erupt in the Republic but are short, sporatic and everything quickly returns to just another normal day.  In Kytan however, it is occupied by the Republic.  The whole port economy of the East is disrupted and collapsed, Port Fredrick and Kytan are both plummitted into brutal recessions which leave most people homeless and jobless.<br>
<br>
Most Easterners are opposed to the Republic.  H-Corp however has met a massive boom in the East.  Gibralter tursn into a massive prison complex because of the Kytan massacre, it houses criminals from all over the East.<br>
<br>
Then they discover the elves adn blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway.  The Questions:<br>
<br>
-The Republic is bad, bordering on the grey because the yare reluctant to do soem things.  The Senate is corrupt and so is the Emperor.<br>
<br>
-Locke is a elf warrior, the strongest by far, and also quite unstable, he vanished a while back after some things happen with his GF, but makes several appearances during the game timeline.<br>
<br>
-She finds a boy wandering around in the debris looking for his folks.  Since only a part of the shanty town was destroy, there are survivors from other parts who will probably take him in though he's not really part of the story afterwards, you really don't know what happens to him except that our hero killed his family and friends by destroying the prison complex(which she does because it's the main sign of the presence of the Republic). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umastahtheeph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mastah Theeph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/10/02 8:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=791.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm...</span><hr size=1> It's really cool... I like.<br>
